article.description: — Great Osobor scored 17 points as Utah State beat Northwest Nazarene 84-53 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Osobor's 17 help Utah State defeat Northwest Nazarene 84-53
article.linkText: Osobor's 17 help Utah State defeat Northwest Nazarene 84-53
article.story: LOGAN, Utah -- — Great Osobor scored 17 points as Utah State beat Northwest Nazarene 84-53 on Saturday night. Osobor had 10 rebounds for the Aggies (9-1). Mason Falslev added 14 points while going 7 of 11 from the field and also had five assists and four steals. Isaac Johnson was 4-of-5 shooting and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line to finish with 13 points. The Aggies extended their winning streak to eight games. The Nighthawks were led by Easton Reagan, who recorded 12 points. Northwest Nazarene also got 11 points from Aaron Murphy. In addition, Christian Rose finished with 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
